programme.title: Man Beast
programme.desc: Connie Hayward mounts an expedition into the Himalayan Mountains looking for her brother, who has not returned from a previous trek trying to locate the Yeti, or "Abominable Snowman". Arriving at her brother's last-known camp Connie and her companions find only a strange old guide, Varga. They are soon attacked by gigantic Snowmen but are not half as surprised as when Vargas reveals his secret origin and the plans he has for Connie.

programme.title: Skin (1961)
programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. This game show is sure to make you laugh as contestants struggle to keep up with Marx’s lightning-quick wit and goofy antics.

programme.title: The Big Seventeen
programme.desc: Upper middle-class teenagers in Los Angeles are going crazy. They trash a movie theater, beating up the manager and pushing a young man through a plate glass window. Sergeant Friday must get to the bottom of what is causing this to happen.

programme.title: Front Runner (1959)
programme.desc: Two rival jockeys faceoff at the racetrack, but one of them may have an advantage after an unexpected run in with the supernatural.

programme.title: Face of Murder (1959)
programme.desc: Mike sets up an interview with a man who has been convicted of five murders and is currently waiting for his scheduled execution. When the two meet, the prisoner makes an escape attempt and takes Mike and a priest hostage.

programme.title: Death at Dawn
programme.desc: After Farmer Perkins murders a store clerk in front of his wife, and is allowed to walk after his trial, the Cartwright's step in to make sure he'll be rearrested, tried, and hung.

programme.title: Jed Buys the Freeway
programme.desc: Henry Jones shows up at the Clampett's pretending to be an old friend.

programme.title: The Case of the Jolly Hangman
programme.desc: A traveling salesman is found hanged in his hotel room. The police eventually rule it to be a suicide, but his widow thinks otherwise, and asks Holmes to investigate the further.

programme.title: Breath of Life
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: Four the Hard Way
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: Folk Song Festival
programme.desc: When the hotel hosts a children's song festival, Stanley takes charge of the Italian group.

programme.title: The Matchmaker
programme.desc: The Andersons host a party for Margaret's cousin Louise and her boyfriend Tom, hoping there is a proposal in the future.

programme.title: Bad Man of Deadwood (1941)
programme.desc: Roy Rogers and Gabby Hayes are together again in this Republic Pictures gem. This time they’re trying to set up a medicine show in Deadwood, a town known for dangerous entrepreneurs who don’t like competition. Sally Payne is on-hand as a member of the troop where Roy and Gabby work as entertainers, while Carol Adams plays a reporter who may have a romantic interest in Roy. Songs include ‘Song of the Dusty Trail’, and ‘Home on the Rangeland’.

programme.title: Report from the Aleutians
programme.desc: A filmic record of US military operations on the Aleutian Island of Adak to take back Japanese occupied Kiska. Though uncredited, John Huston (The Maltese Falcon) directed this documentary, which also features music by four time Oscar winner Dimitri Tiomkin (High Noon, The Old Man and the Sea). Director Huston, who also helped narrate the film and was actually in the Army Signal Corps at the time of filming, wanted to use this documentary to show the everyday life of American soldiers. Though the US Army initially objected, Huston got his way...

programme.title: The Road to Hollywood (1947)
programme.desc: Bing Crosby fans will be intrigued by this selection of scenes from early Crosby shorts woven together to create a fictional biography of one Hollywood’s biggest stars. Director Bud Pollard appears as the narrator, while the king of the crooners sings such songs as ‘One More Chance’, and ‘Wrap Your troubles in Dreams’.

programme.title: Renegade Girl
programme.desc: Ann Shelby, who's family is allied with the notorious William Quantrill, lives life as an outlaw to exact revenge on the murder of her brother.

programme.title: The Fabulous Dorseys (1947)
programme.desc: Tommy and Jimmy Dorsey play themselves in this high-spirited film biography. The film follows the brothers from their early days all the way to their greatest successes. Director Alfred E. Green ("The Jolson Story") uses the film as a showcase for some great music, including "I'm Getting Sentimental Over You" and "Marie." Jazz buffs will notice cameos by such greats as bandleader Paul Whiteman and pianist Art Tatum. In fact, look for a special jam session featuring the Dorseys and Tatum. It's a perfect snapshot of the days when musicians could really swing.

programme.title: Hazel's People (Happy as the Grass Was Green)
programme.desc: A Mennonite boy is beaten to death at an unnamed NY university protesting the Vietnam War. His best friend and another college student, Eric Mills, attends his funeral in the Mennonite country in Pennsylvania.

programme.title: International Crime (1938)
programme.desc: A multifaceted mystery full of shocking twists and turns, this is one of the earliest onscreen appearances of the detective figure known as “The Shadow.” The story follows Lamont Cranston (Rod La Rocque), an amateur criminologist and detective who gets tangled up in a web of deception and danger when he sets out to capture an infamous safe cracker. A wildly popular print and radio character birthed in pulp novels of the 1930s, The Shadow left such an enduring impression on the American public that he spawned a film adaptation starring Alec Baldwin more than 60 years after the character’s genesis.

programme.title: Torture Ship
programme.desc: This low budget screamer from Sigmund Neufeld Productions stars Lyle Talbot and Irving Pichel in a story of a mad scientist performing cruel experiments on board his private ship. His plan is to learn about the criminal mind, and what better way than to...well, you know. Obviously, this isn’t the Love Boat! Victor Halperin (White Zombie) directed this tale based on a story by none other than Jack London. Sit back and enjoy. Just don’t let the man with the scalpel near your head!

programme.title: Episode 5
programme.desc: Groucho, Chico and Harpo graced the small screen in the 1950s appearing in a myriad of variety programs, sitcoms, and game shows. The Marx Brothers TV Collection features long-lost material from this wide array of appearances.

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 2
programme.desc: Guest starring Sid Caesar in a series of comedy skits.

programme.title: Season 29 Episode 160
programme.desc: Comedian Johnny Carson hosts a variety of celebrities in his iconic late night talk show.

programme.title: Jam Handy to the Rescue
programme.desc: A satirical exploration of the life and career of educational film pioneer, Henry Jamison Handy.

programme.title: Bloodlust
programme.desc: A wealthy recluse with a love of hunting the ultimate game... people! Based off of Richard Connell's short story, The Most Dangerous Game, this thrilling tale is surely one you won't want to miss. Follow the two unlucky couples that accidently come across Dr. Albert Balleau's (Wilton Graff) private island. Through initially friendly to the group, this tropical island is not what it appears, and Balleau's true devises are revealed. Will any of these young adventurers survive? Or will the sadistic hunter live to kill another day? Find out in Ralph Brooke's, Bloodlust!

programme.title: Man in the Attic (1953)
programme.desc: Jack Palance stars as a mysterious man suspected of being the notorious Jack the Ripper! Palance plays a research pathologist in 1888 London, seeking to rent a quiet attic room for his “experiments.”

programme.title: Fog Island
programme.desc: This strange mystery tale stars two of Hollywood's greatest villains - George Zucco and Lionel Atwill. Zucco (The Mad Ghoul, The Mummy's Ghost) is Leo Grainer, a former convict living on an island with his daughter. Seeking revenge on his old business partners, he lures them to his home where they are soon at his mercy. This forgotten nugget from Producers Releasing Corporation was directed by Terry O. Morse (Godzilla, King of the Monsters) and is an excellent example of the "old dark house" mysteries from Hollywood's Poverty Row.

programme.title: Murder By Television (1935)
programme.desc: When the inventor of a new method of sending television signals refuses to sell his ideas to television companies, he turns up dead! Bela Lugosi stars (and is the prime suspect) in this perfect story of a perfect crime.

programme.title: The Ape Man
programme.desc: This campy yet compelling horror classic stars none other than the legendary Bela Lugosi as Dr. James Brewster who embarks on an ill-fated endeavor to find an antidote after he turns himself into a hairy, stooped-over ape-man. When Dr. Brewster discovers that the key ingredient of the antidote is recently drawn human spinal fluid, he is abandoned by his assistant and must rely on the help of his captive gorilla to aid him in his search for an appropriate donor.

programme.title: Money (1959)
programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. This game show is sure to make you laugh as contestants struggle to keep up with Marx’s lightning-quick wit and goofy antics.

programme.title: The Big September Man (1952)
programme.desc: Someone murdered a secretary late at night in her office. She was beaten to death with a metal pipe wrapped in newspaper. Could it be the drunk found three blocks away beating his head against a wall?

programme.title: The Riddle (1959)
programme.desc: While traveling through India, a couple runs into a beggar who seems to be acting differently from the other beggars in the area. The husband is convinced that the beggar is trying to kill them.

programme.title: Mute Evidence (1959)
programme.desc: Invited to visit a retired doctor, Mike arrives only to discover that the doctor has gone missing. The only person that knows anything about the doctor’s whereabouts is the doctor’s deaf, mute ward.

programme.title: The Abduction
programme.desc: Little Joe's date, Jennifer, is abducted and held for ransom at the circus. He and Hoss search the circus for her, facing a tough crowd of carnies in their search.

programme.title: Jed Becomes a Banker
programme.desc: Jed is hired to pretend to be an employee when Mr. Drysdale needs a crack shot to one-up a rival banker.

programme.title: The Case of the Imposter Mystery (1955)
programme.desc: With Holmes and Watson out of London, an impersonator takes their place.

programme.title: A Time to Be Alive
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: The Tony Morelli Story
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: Army Buddies
programme.desc: Stanley grapples with his conscience when his old army buddies seek vengeance against an innocent comrade.

programme.title: Bud the Bridesmaid
programme.desc: The Andersons prepare for cousin Louise's wedding.

programme.title: Hurricane Horseman
programme.desc: Lane Chandler plays a gunsmith who offers a trade with a band of criminals. If he fixes their guns, they must release their hostage.

programme.title: Tombstone Canyon
programme.desc: Ken Maynard stars as Ken Mason in this 1932 western classic. While passing through Tombstone Canyon, Ken learns about the Phantom who may be the key to unearthing the mystery of his heritage.

programme.title: The General (1926)
programme.desc: Buster Keaton's comedy about a railroad engineer's battle with union spies is considered one of the greatest films of all time. Co-written and co-directed by Keaton, its breakneck chase scenes are as riveting as anything ever put on the silver screen. Keaton always mentioned this movie as his favorite, and we can still see why. Also starring Marion Mack as Buster's beloved, though some might say he loves his locomotive more than the girl!

programme.title: My Outlaw Brother (1951)
programme.desc: My Outlaw Brother features Mickey Rooney as Denny O'Moore, a young man who learns his brother has joined up with a ruthless Mexican bandit known as "El Tigre." This tense western drama from director Elliot Nugent (My Favorite Brunette, The Male Animal) also features Robert Stack, Robert Preston, and Wanda Hendrix as Senorita Carmel Alvarado, the alluring woman who comes between the brothers. Can Danny, his brother, and Carmen fend off El Tigre and his gang? Watch and find out!

programme.title: Santa Fe Trail (1940)
programme.desc: Oscar winner Michael Curtiz (Casablanca, Mildred Pierce) directed this exciting drama about Army officer “Jeb” Stuart and the days leading up to the Civil War. Errol Flynn (The Adventures of Robin Hood) stars as Stuart, with Olivia de Havilland as his romantic interest (the seventh of nine times they were paired together by Warner Bros.) The cast includes Ronald Reagan as General George Custer, and Raymond Massey as John Brown, with such familiar faces as Alan Hale and Van Hefflin in supporting roles. Filmed partly in Santa Fe!

programme.title: The Lost World
programme.desc: Arthur Conan Doyle’s epic tale comes to life in this classic from the silent era. Bessie Love, Lewis Stone, and Wallace Beery star as explorers who learn that dinosaurs still exist in South America. Of course, the expedition can’t end without them trying to bring a prehistoric creature back to London, which results in catastrophe. This was the first full ­length feature film to utilize stop­motion animation in the creation of its creatures. The painstaking process perfectly enables us to see the mighty prehistoric monsters clash with modern lovers in a most remarkable story of love, romance, and amazing adventure!

programme.title: The Death Kiss (1932)
programme.desc: Bela Lugosi was fresh off the success of Dracula when he appeared in this low-budget murder mystery for director Edwin L. Marin (Tall in the Saddle, The Invisible Agent) It’s set in the world of movies, where an actor is killed during a production. Having been involved with most of the women connected with the studio, there are plenty of suspects! Along with Lugosi the cast includes David Manners, Adrienne Ames, and John Wray.

programme.title: Beast from Haunted Cave (Friday Fright)
programme.desc: A giant spider stalks a band of thieves in this schlocky thriller from Gene Corman Productions. The story follows gangster Alexander Ward and his crew as they enlist the help of a local ski-instructor in the heist of several gold bars. But when they use explosives to create a distraction, they disturb the lair of a massive spider! Monte Hellman, the man behind such cult favorites as Two-Lane Blacktop, made his directorial debut with Beast From Haunted Cave. Trivia note: This movie debuted on a double bill with The Wasp Woman.

programme.title: Elvira's Movie Macabre: Gamera, Super Monster
programme.desc: Elvira presents the 1980 Sci-Fi Action film Gamera, Super Monster. The film features a prehistoric turtle who serves as Earth's last hope in the face of giant monsters.

programme.title: Island Claws
programme.desc: When a biological experiment goes terribly wrong, scientists unleash a legion of giant killer crabs.

programme.title: Drive-In Massacre
programme.desc: You'll Pay To Get In... And Pray To Get Out! Two detectives are hell-bent on capturing a demented killer who has been stalking a California drive-in! The film's original poster featured the following: "DRIVE-IN MASSACRE has been deemed by an independent film board to be too terrifying for viewing by the average theatre patron. For this reason, it is suggested that those of you with severe emotional disorders or chronic coronary dysfunction NOT see this movie. The risk is entirely yours." You can't say you haven't been warned!

programme.title: Brother, Cry for Me
programme.desc: Three brothers searching for Inca treasure resort to kidnapping, extortion and murder in this independent thriller. Starring Steve Drexel, Larry Parnell, and Leslie Parrish...

programme.title: The Vampire Bat (1933)
programme.desc: An excellent cast featuring Lionel Atwill, Fay Wray, Melvyn Douglas, and the immortal Dwight Frye headline this macabre tale of vampire attacks in a small village. Does a troubled man-child with an affection for bats have something to do with it? Or is it a local scientist who appears to know quite a bit about vampirism? Director Frank R. Strayer spins a thrilling tale from Hugo nominated screenwriter Edward T. Lowe (House of Frankenstein, House of Dracula) and will have you craving more films from the first golden age of horror!

programme.title: Great Generals - Gen. George Patton
programme.desc: Documentary on General George Patton narrated by Ronald Reagan.

programme.title: Prelude to War
programme.desc: The official testament from the US Government during World War II underscoring why we must fight the various enemies of the Allies

programme.title: The Great Dan Patch (1949)
programme.desc: The Great Dan Patch thunders across the screen in the tradition of great horse movies like Seabiscuit and National Velvet, combining the talents of an all­star cast that includes Dennis O’Keefe, Gail Russell and Henry Hull. But you’ll be hearing more than hoof beats, because there’s plenty of romance in this forgotten treasure from director Joseph Newman (This Island Earth, The Big Circus).

programme.title: Sing Cowboy Sing (1937)
programme.desc: Tex Ritter stars in this rip­roarin’ saga of the Old West! This time, Tex and his pal Duke (played by silent screen veteran Al St. John) square off against a ruthless gang trying to take over the territory’s freight hauling business.The cast includes Snub Pollard, Horace Murphy, and one of the great Poverty Row movie villains of the day, Karl Hackett. Songs include "I’m a Natural Born Cowboy," and "Goodbye Old Paint, I’m ­Leavin’ Cheyenne"...

programme.title: Las Vegas Hillbillys
programme.desc: Ferlin Husky plays a singer who works with a barmaid (Mamie Van Doren) to turn an old Las Vegas casino into a showcase for country music.

programme.title: The Alphabet Conspiracy
programme.desc: A little girl grows frustrated with her homework and dreams the Mad Hatter and Jabberwock of Alice in Wonderland fame have come to abolish the alphabet. Stanley Adams, Frank Baxter, and Hans Conried star in this whimsical tale for director Robert Sinclair (That Wonderful Urge) For trivia buffs: This originally aired on NBC as part of a Bell Telephone educational series, and earned an Emmy for cinematography...

programme.title: Bill and Coo
programme.desc: This peculiar ‘movie’ won an Honorary Oscar in 1948 for its careful blending of “artistry and patience…” Alas, it didn’t inspire more movies acted out by birds. In this one, prolific screenwriter Dean Riesner stepped into the director’s seat for the first and only time, guiding a cast of birdies to tell the story of a town called "Chirpendale," where the peaceful residents are being terrorized by an evil black crow known as "The Black Menace." You’ll have to see it to believe it, but you’ll be charmed by this long forgotten gem.

programme.title: Mr. Imperium (1951)
programme.desc: Lana Turner plays an entertainer who falls for a Crown Prince (Ezio Pinza) in this musical romance from MGM. Marjorie Main, Barry Sullivan, Cedric Harwicke, and Debbie Reynolds also star in this feature directed by two time Oscar nominee Don Hartman (Road to Morocco, The Gay Deception), and boasting music by one of America’s great composers, Harold Arlen! Songs include ‘Andiamo’, ‘Let Me Look At You’, and ‘My Man and My Mule’. (Turner’s voice is dubbed by Trudy Erwin, one of Hollywood’s top ‘uncredited’ singers!)

programme.title: Nothing Sacred (1937)
programme.desc: This classic screwball comedy stars Carole Lombard as Hazel Flagg, a small-town girl who's dying of radiation poisoning. Recognizing the kind of story that sells newspapers, reporter Wally Cook (Fredric March) whisks Hazel off to New York City and turns her into a media sensation. Wally's self-serving plan becomes more complicated when he starts falling for Hazel. Pioneering three-strip Technicolor and smartly written by Ben Hecht and James H. Street, "Nothing Sacred" is a sophisticated comedy brilliantly taking on the media's tendency to put profit before dignity and the simple truth.

programme.title: Father Steps Out (1937)
programme.desc: Joe Hardcastle has it all...a blossoming cheese business...a wife who loves him...and the respect of all around him. Yet, when some society swindlers step in, it's his chauffer that steps in to save the day! Starring George Carney, Bruce Seton, and Dinah Sheridan, this is a "gouda" RKO comedy you won't want to miss!

programme.title: Kansas City Confidential (1952)
programme.desc: In "Kansas City Confidential," four robbers hold up an armored truck, getting away with over a million dollars in cash. Joe Rolfe (John Payne), a down-on-his-luck delivery driver who is accused of involvement in the heist, sets out to discover who set him up and to exact revenge. He follows a trail that leads him to a web of hired killers and corrupt police in Mexico. "Kansas City Confidential" was the source of inspiration for Quentin Tarantino's "Reservoir Dogs." An imaginative film noir classic, this is a fast-paced and highly entertaining gem!

programme.title: Get That Man

programme.title: Long Hair of Death

Her beautiful older daughter knows the real reason for the execution lies in the lord's sexual desire for her mother. After confronting the lord on the matter, she, too, is killed. A much younger daughter is spared and taken in by her mother's killers. Once she is of age, as a horrible, deadly plague sweeps the land, she marries the lord's worthless son. Then, during a brutal thunderstorm, the older daughter mysteriously reappears and begins to avenge her mother's death.

programme.title: Manhattan Night of Murder

programme.title: Battle of the Worlds

programme.title: Dementia 13 (1963)

Secrets shroud Kathleen's demise, and soon there is a mysterious interloper prowling the grounds with a big axe to grind. Genuinely engaging and well-photographed, "Dementia 13" is a bone-chilling horror classic sure to thrill horror enthusiasts and Coppola fans alike.

programme.title: The Guys Next Door
programme.desc: Who, among us, can say that we come from a “normal” family? The Guys Next Door, a feature length documentary, offers an alternative to the traditional ideas of what constitute the nuclear American family. Meet Erik and Sandro, a gay couple with two daughters birthed by their friend Rachel with donor eggs. In her 40s, Rachel is married to Tony and they have three biological children of their own. Rachel and Tony, a seemingly traditional married couple, live in the suburbs of Massachusetts with their children. Inspired by a TV program about the difficulties and costs associated with gay couples having children, Rachel, age 41, volunteers to be a surrogate – not once, but twice within two years – for Erik, her good friend from college, and his husband Sandro, an Italian émigré. This film begins when Rachel is eight months pregnant with Erik and Sandro’s second daughter, Eleonora. What compels a woman in her forties with three children of her own to carry children for friends? What is the reaction of her husband and children? And, how will Erik and Sandro handle the challenges of parenting two girls in a world that still emphasizes the importance of maternal instinct? The issues raised in this film - gay marriage and parenting, surrogacy as a path for gays and lesbians to have children, and the extension and redefinition of what it means to be “an American family" - remain relevant as our country is a cultural battleground during the divisive 2016 presidential election. The Guys Next Door is a powerful antidote to the negative backlash and hateful rhetoric aimed at same sex families. In the words of the esteemed documentary filmmaker Ross McElwee (Sherman’s March), “with nuance, verve and humor, this film goes well beyond issues of surrogacy and gay parenthood and explores the humanity that connects us all."

programme.desc: Roping and riding across North America, the International Gay Rodeo Association's courageous cowboys and cowgirls brave challenges both in and out of the arena on their quest to qualify for the World Finals. Along the way, they’ll bust every stereotype in the book. The film tells the story of five members of the IGRA. From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider who’s never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, “QUEENS & COWBOYS” weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.

programme.title: Unlikely Family
programme.desc: Follow this Unlikely Family as it challenges the archaic ideology that being openly gay - and Christian - is incompatible.

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

programme.title: The Q Agenda

Writer-director duo Leita Solomon and Wes Akuobi talk about their controversial film, "The Cypher." Plus, we discuss the departure of Vanderpump Rules cast members after racist comments.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: Culture Q is the world’s first weekly queer-centric news series brought to you by the leading global queer streaming network, Revry. This innovative, weekly news series creatively features entertainment, pop culture, lifestyle and political news with wit and insightfully nuanced perspectives. Emphasizing the queer millieu, Culture Q stands to be the leading, weekly forum for boundary-pushing discussions and commentary. Hosted by digital news influencer pioneers, Shira Lazar and Andy Lalwani of the highly successful What’s Trending, Culture Q will feature an ever-changing cavalcade of guests who help capture that X-factor which defines queer culture.

programme.title: Equality U
programme.desc: Equality U is a feature-length documentary following 34 young activists on the Soulforce Equality Ride. At some stops they're welcomed with open arms, at others they're arrested for trespassing or for simply attempting to open up a dialog. At every stop, they're connecting with young people who've often never met an openly gay, lesbian, bisexual or transgender person who is comfortable with who they are.

programme.title: The Most Dangerous Year
programme.desc: As a dark wave of anti-transgender “bathroom bills” began sweeping across the nation, The Human Rights Campaign called 2016 the most dangerous year ever for transgender Americans. Filmmaker Vlada Knowlton captured the ensuing civil rights battle from the perspective of a group of embattled parents – including herself and her husband, parents of a young trans girl -- fighting to protect their children from discriminatory laws in their home state. While Knowlton passionately follows the story of anti-transgender legislation, the heart of the film lies in the stories of the families who accept and support their kids for exactly who they are.

programme.title: Raid Of The Rainbow Lounge
programme.desc: A riveting recount of a violent 2009 raid of a Texas gay bar and its aftermath. Following sordid allegations and outrage, Fort Worth emerged a leader in LGBT equality. Experience the journey as told by the victims and those who helped change the city.

programme.title: BIFL
programme.desc: Expectations, different shades of intimacy, & what it really means to love someone.

programme.title: Happy Birthday Marsha
programme.desc: Happy Birthday, Marsha! is a film about iconic transgender artist and activist, Marsha "Pay it No Mind" Johnson, and her life in the hours before she ignited the 1969 Stonewall Riots in New York City.

programme.title: Voguing The Message
programme.desc: A pre-Madonna primer that raises questions about race, sex and subcultural style, Voguing: The Message traces the roots of this gay Black and Latino dance form, which appropriates and plays with poses and images from mainstream fashion.

programme.title: Erin's Guide To Kissing Girls
programme.desc: Erin, a spunky 12 year old, is on a mission to woo the coolest girl in school, but will it put a strain on her friendship with her BFF, Liz?

programme.title: Frameline Voices
programme.desc: A collection of LGBTQ youth-centered shorts with something for audiences of all ages, from the awkward animated memories of Were You Gay in Highschool? to the inspirational story of Zachariah George, aka Mr. Navajo.

programme.title: Suicide Kale
programme.desc: While having lunch with another couple, new couple Jasmine and Penny stumble upon an anonymous suicide note and proceed to work to uncover the identity of the author.

programme.title: Gayborhood
programme.desc: S1 E1 | Adrian’s event doesn’t go as expected. Leacy prepares a first date. Sethe unveils his new art installation and it leaves D’ante with questions. Casey’s hook up isn’t quite what he expected and Blaine has problems adjusting.

programme.title: Strut
programme.desc: In each episode of Strut, we watch Eddie and her friends transform through their risky new endeavor in unexpected positive ways. Eddie is a geeky porn editor whose low self-confidence has turned her into a 26-year-old hermit. Her friends, Eva (an unemployed artist), Lucy (an intern), and Chandaleer (a trainwreck/fashion model) vow to save her from her unhealthy solitude. When the friends decide to start a high-end escorting agency to earn more money, they convince skeptical Eddie to help them build their business and lift her self-esteem. Together they successfully navigate the adrenaline-fueled escorting industry with Eddie as their CEO and fellow sex worker.

programme.title: Out On Stage
programme.desc: Out On Stage is THE absolutely hilarious and one-of-a-kind, originally produced comedy hosted by Zach Noe Towers! See OUT Magazine's "1 of the 10 comedians to watch in 2018," the comedian that Sarah Silverman calls, "So, SO, SO Funny" and 17 other top-rated Gay and Lesbian stand-up comedians discuss taboo subjects as only they can!

programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

programme.desc: Miguel is a fisherman in a tiny Peruvian village where traditions run deep. He is married to the lovely Mariela and about to be a father, but has a secret love affair with Santiago, a painter, who is ostracized by the town because he's gay. After a tragic accident occurs, Miguel must choose between sentencing Santiago to eternal torment or doing right by him and, in turn, revealing their relationship to Mariela and the entire village.

With insufficient public awareness of the benefits of psychedelic product/services, and steep competition with bloated Big Pharma advertising budgets, building brand recognition is of the utmost importance. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - Social Club TV and what it is specialize in - - Big Pharma’s TV advertising spend - - The psychedelics industry has infinitely more regulatory hurdles (Schedule I) and product/service stigma to cut through - - Social Club TV CEO Joshua Otten knows how critical structured advertising is to branding success. - - Big Pharma expertise

programme.title: Canada Cultivation and Mushroom Editing

Today we have Damon Michaels with us to discuss some of the recent news that’s come out for Mydecine including Health Canada’s approval of the expansion of their cultivation facilities here in Canada. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - Canadian expansion means that Mydecine has “instant access” and allows them to supply clinical trials says Michaels - - The possibility of editing mushrooms - - Mydecine facility in Canada probably won’t scale to meet a commercial need, says Michaels - - The roadmap for the next 12 months? Proving efficacy and safety – and looking at protocols

programme.title: Microdosing, PTSD, and a Growing Industry
programme.desc: Earlier this week we had COO Damon Michaels at The Dales Report to discuss some of the recent news that’s come out for Mydecine (NEO: MYCO) (OTCMKTS: MYCOF). Continuing on with his interview, Michaels tells us about the addressable market for PTSD, how quickly the industry for psychedelics is moving, and how big pharma may get involved. - This is part two of the interview. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - Michaels says that psychedelics usage for PTSD market may grow rapidly, doesn’t just have to be for veterans - - Texas Senate considering a bill to study the effectiveness of psychedelics in therapy – exciting news, says Michaels - - Psychedelics industry moving 6-7x as fast as cannabis

programme.title: Numinus NASDAQ Listing?
programme.desc: Last week, The Dales Report sat down with Numinus (TSXV: NUMI) CEO Payton Nyquvest to discuss some of the company’s latest milestones and learn about what the company will be working on over the summer. Nyquvest said “exciting times” are ahead for the burgeoning industry. - Numinus was recently granted Tier 1 issuer status on the TSX venture exchange. Nyquvest said he’s hopeful that the company will receive its own investment bank coverage in the near future. - Here’s some highlights from the interview: - - Tier 1 gives the opportunity to move fairly quickly in terms of more significant up listings: TSX and a potential NASDAQ listing. - - Numinus is not in a rush to proceed NASDAQ listing, especially after witnessing other companies in the industry fail to follow through. - - Looking ahead, what the latter half of 2021 will look like for the company. - - The CEO also touched on the results of a recent study conducted by MAPS published in Nature.

programme.title: Ep. 14 - The Untold History: How Africa Brought Cannabis to the Americas

Experts in the fields of history, geography, anthropology, and archaeology are uncovering new findings on how people of all cultures integrated cannabis in their societies. Chris Duvall is a professor of Geography at the University of New Mexico and he is the author of, The African Roots of Marijuana. His research is opening a new perspective on how cannabis comes to Africa and spreads across the continent. Centuries of lost history are coming to light because of Chris's diligent research. Aspiring academics with a passion for cannabis will not want to miss this episode.

programme.desc: Certification for sustainable, naturally-grown agriculture, Clean Green Certified is the closest to “Organic” that the cannabiz can get. We're honored to welcome founder Chris Van Hook. Together, we explore the value of certification for industry operators, consumers and the planet. Chris offers tips and tricks that you can put to use in your own garden. Dig in! Founded in 2004, Swami Select has had the pleasure of being Clean Green Certified since 2011.

programme.title: Meet the International Canna Farmer's Association Chair, Kristin Nevedal
programme.desc: We're honored to welcome to today's show, Kristin Nevedal, International Cannabis Farmer's Association Chair. The International Cannabis Farmer’s Association strives to empower traditional Cannabis farmers through education, research and advocacy. Their programs raise public awareness about the benefits of traditionally farmed Cannabis and provide educational resources for farmers, regulators, industry and consumers. They advocate for the development of responsible regulations in CA, which are seen as crucially important due to the state’s significance to national and international policy development. They will promote public policy that ensures an equal share of licenses are issued to traditional sun grown Cannabis farmers. They conduct research to quantify the ecological superiority of traditionally farmed Cannabis as well as gathering data necessary to establish internationally recognized appellations of origin. They create a dynamic and creative consumer direct educational campaign that highlights the quality and ecological superiority of traditionally farmed sun grown Cannabis.

programme.title: What's It Like to Judge The Emerald Cup - Go Backstage with Swami Select
programme.desc: Founded in 2003, Northern California’s Emerald Cup advances the concept of sustainable, outdoor farming of medical cannabis. Longtime advocates of the spiritually and physically healing potential of regeneratively-grown cannabis, Swami Select founders Nikki Lastreto and Swami Chaitanya have judged The Emerald Cup’s flower competition since the event began. As the largest, organic, outdoor, medicinal cannabis competition in the world, The Cup advances our movement by cross-pollinating cultivators, patients and patrons with scientific and agriculture experts who work across industries. Now a global movement, the community celebration honors the year’s best, sun-grown, medicinal cannabis producers.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Atty Ben Crump

From Trayvon Martin to Michael Brown, Crump continues to push the envelope for justice for those whose lives have been changed due an unfair legal system.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Erika Alexander
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is the brilliant actress from “The Cosby Show” and the 90’s hit series “Living Single” – Erika Alexander. Erika is a producer on the upcoming documentary “John Lewis: Good Trouble” which will release on July 3. DL, Jasmine, and Erika have a great discussion about the creating of “Living Single” and how the show “Friends” became a bigger hit after using the same concept. Erika gives great insight into racism in the entertainment industry.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Leonard Pitts
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is Pulitzer Prize Winner and columnist for the Miami Herald Leonard Pitts, Jr. Leonard Pitts has a progressive voice in journalism who dives deep into the racial and cultural issues of society.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Matt Barnes

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Tamika Mallory
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is activist and the former chair of the Women’s March Tamika Mallory. Currently she is the co-founder of the social justice organization Until Freedom. DL, Jasmine, and Tamika share a deep discussion of the after effects of George Floyd’s murder by police, protests, and where civil unrest is headed in America.

programme.title: DL Hughley Uncut - Guest Willy T Ribbs
programme.desc: Guest on DL Uncut is former race car driver Willy T. Ribbs. Willy was the first African American to test a Formula One racing car and first African American to compete in the Indy 500. DL, Jasmine and Willy discuss the sport of auto racing, the lack of diversity, and the future of sport in the changing times of America.

programme.title: Not Another Black Movie
programme.desc: Not Another Black Movie stars Damon Williams (Bad Boys of Comedy, Comic View, BET LIVE, The Tom Joyner Morning Show), Janet Hubert (The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air), Rodney Perry (The Monique Show, Who's Got Jokes) Jay Davis (Not Another Zombie Movie, Shots Fired), and Leon Rogers (WGCI, Comic View, Bad Boys of Comedy). - Not Another Black Movie is not only a spoof of a genre often associated with Tyler Perry films, but a satirical look at family dysfunction as well. Written by Jay Davis and Directed by Donte "Diesel" Williams, Not Another Black Movie addresses issues that effect many families whether they be rich or poor, black or white. Although we poke fun at some of the stereotypical roles portrayed in this genre, we hope to shed some light on problems that plague many families while giving you a good laugh.

programme.title: Jupiter
programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.

programme.title: Hobart Tasmaina
programme.desc: In Tasmania, Jason immerses himself into the natural world by visiting Cradle Mountain and Weindorfer’s Forest Walk. He also experiences Hobart's cafe culture, and goes on the hunt for fresh seafood.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: S9E5 - Oaxaca, the Land of Seven Moles
programme.desc: So many moles, so little time. Rick will focus on two moles while visiting the Seasons of My Heart Cooking School on the outskirts of Oaxaca City to explore Black Mole and Green Mole with school owner Susana Trilling and her students.

programme.title: S9E6 - Delicious Eco-Tourism
programme.desc: Ever on a quest to learn more about food, Rick even vacations with a food-oriented agenda. Join him in the mountains of Finca Las Nieves, with its artisanal coffee production and organic gardens, and learn about sustainable gardening.

programme.title: S9E7 - The Kernel of Deliciousness
programme.desc: The variety of corns available in Oaxaca boggles the mind and the taste buds. Rick introduces us to Amado Ramirez Leyva who believes that corn, domesticated some 9,000 years ago in Mexico, represents the very foundation of Mexican culture.

programme.title: S9E8 - Mercado Madness
programme.desc: “You are what you eat.” Brillat Savarin’s statement fuels Rick’s tour of the 21 de Noviembre market in downtown Oaxaca. We uncover the incredibly rich culture of the market and its role in the daily lives and meals of the local population.

programme.title: S9E9 - Oaxacan Cheese Primer
programme.desc: In Mexico, cheese is all about freshness, and fresh cheese is exactly what Rick has found in the village of Rojas where he and two local women turn uber-fresh milk from alfalfa-fed cows into queso fresco and salty quesillo (string cheese).

programme.title: S9E10 - Puerto Escondido: Living the Dream
programme.desc: Ever dream of renting a space with a kitchen in Mexico just to cook all the fresh fish you can eat? Rick lives the dream at Hotel Villas Carrizalillo in Puerto Escondido. With few culinary tools, and fresh ingredients, it is time to feast.

programme.title: Catalina Island
programme.desc: Catalina Island, California is a unique island off the coast of California, and Donna will take you on a journey there to revel in the island’s history, art, cuisine, and have some fun horseback riding.

programme.title: From Myanmar to Scotland
programme.desc: Biodiversity is a central component to the successful operation of Earth’s natural systems. Meet people from Haiti, Myanmar, Honduras, Kenya, Canada, and Scotland who spend time and energy securing healthy local environmental regulations.

programme.title: From Liberia to Mongolia
programme.desc: What we take from and put back into the Earth reflects the very nature of who we are as human beings. Meet people from Washington, Liberia, Macedonia, the Cook Islands, Mongolia, and Chile who believe end results depend upon how we begin.

programme.title: France's Via Aquitania
programme.desc: Follow the Via Aquitania, an ancient Roman road that connected a network of cities and was the main trade route between the Mediterranean Sea and the Atlantic Ocean. Traces of the region’s history abound and will become clearer to you the more you hear the people who love this land speak of it.

programme.title: The Route of the Two Oceans
programme.desc: The thin ridge that links the two Americas is a miniature world unto itself and concentrates a vast amount of diversity into a small area of land. Follow the Inter-American Highway from Panama City to the Isthmus of Rivas in Nicaragua, the narrowest ridge of Central America.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: So Much Vodka, So Little Time
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony continues his mission with a tour of local working-class specialties. He tries his hand at ice-fishing, drinks a lot of vodka, feasts on Russian foods, eats smoked fish and ends the outing with a dip in the outdoor cold pool.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance
programme.desc: In Florence, we'll revel in the genius of Michelangelo and Botticelli, climb the dome that kicked off the Renaissance, and cross the Arno to take in modern-day artisan life.

programme.title: S8E4 - Paris Side Trips
programme.desc: After roaming Versailles — the palace of palaces — we'll drop in on exquisite Vaux-le-Vicomte and extravagant Fontainebleau, marvel at Chartres Cathedral...and dine like kings.

programme.title: Wild Travels: America's Oddest Museums
programme.desc: Museums serve a vital purpose in preserving world culture and history, and the clever museums we visit have accomplished the same objective. Walk through the doors of history and visit America’s oddest museums with your host Will Clinger.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: S8E10 - Mexican Microbrews and Pub Fare
programme.desc: Many of us experienced our first Mexican beer on a beach with a squeeze of lime. Now we are happy to see a beer revolution rumbling in the Baja peninsula. Rick takes us from the Tecate brewery to the Tijuana brewery. Salud-

programme.title: Singapore
programme.desc: Join Donna and visit a jewel of an Asian country- Singapore. Experience a place that weaves a confluence of cultures into its fabric, evident in the city’s unique cuisine. Witness acrobat training, explore the fine art of tea, and more.

programme.title: Edinburgh and Scotland
programme.desc: Friendly and feisty, Scotland makes us feel right at home. In Edinburgh, we climb the ramparts of this city's famous castle, shop for kilts, visit mysterious Rosslyn Chapel and gasp on a ghost tour. Then we head to historic St. Andrew's to practice our swing on the world's most famous golf course.

programme.title: Barcelona and Costa Brava
programme.desc: A Mediterranean marvel, Barcelona simmers with beautiful beaches, medieval mazes, eye popping art and hypnotic architecture. From tapas bars, to surrealist art, to Modernist structures, we will feast on Barcelona's delights.

programme.title: Madrid
programme.desc: The Spanish capital Madrid welcomes us with grand plazas and sparkling fountains. First stop is the Prado, one of Europe's great museums and home to Goya, El Greco and Velazquez.

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: Savannah
programme.desc: We visit the old South and enjoy some sweet tea in Savannah. On this episode, we will stroll the city’s beautiful squares, as well as visit its civil war past at Old Fort Jackson. Then, we head up the stairs of the famous Tybee Island lighthouse and visit the Savannah Railroad museum.

programme.title: New Orleans
programme.desc: The saints come marching in as we tour the New Orlean's iconic St. Louis Cathedral and the mysterious Ursuline Convent. We see how floats are made and delve into Mardi Gras history at Mardi Gras World. Finally, we visit the National World War II Museum's world-class collection of memorabilia.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: Disney Animal Kingdom
programme.desc: Explore the process of designing and creating Disney’s Animal Kingdom with incredible behind-the-scenes footage. Discover how Disney incorporates live animals into their attractions and uncover the time taken to create authentic habitats that allow visitors to experience a safari or jungle trek.

programme.title: The Glacier Express and Gornergrat-Bahn
programme.desc: Go sightseeing on the Glacier Express, an extraordinary railway journey high into the Swiss Alps across 291 bridges, through 91 tunnels, and across the Oberalp Pass at the highest point (2,033 meters, or 6,670 feet, above sea level), and, visit the iconic Matterhorn on the Gornergrat-Bahn.

programme.title: Shedd Aquarium: Wild Reef
programme.desc: Experience the wonder of the Shedd Aquarium’s wild reef as light dances off the colorful aquatic sea life that peacefully swim past in the crystal-clear water. Ambient sound makes you feel as if you are deep beneath the ocean.

programme.title: Melbourne Victoria
programme.desc: Jason catches his own lunch at Buxton trout farm, visits a stone fruit orchard, learns how to make sausages at The Green Olive, and learns secrets of cooking from top Australian chef, Guy Grossi.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.desc: It was Walt Disney’s original vision that Disneyland would “never be completed” – always growing and changing. Decades later, Disneyland remains one of the most visited destinations on Earth. Disney Parks has proven its ability remain relevant and continue to be at the very top of the theme parks.

programme.title: S9E11 - Chocolate & Coffee from Bean to Cup
programme.desc: In Mexico, hot chocolate and coffee are equally enjoyed. The Seasons of My Heart Cooking School explains the roasting process from two perspectives, while the Finca Las Nieves Coffee Plantation offers a look into organic coffee production.

programme.title: S9E12 - Bringing Oaxaca Home
programme.desc: The once unknown state of Oaxaca is now on the savvy traveler’s hit list. Its capital is one of Mexico’s most enjoyable colonial cities. Rick takes the spirit of Oaxaca home, and with a group of friends, creates a dinner sure to transport.

programme.title: S9E1 - Oaxaca's Most Magical Holiday
programme.desc: Rick takes us on a remarkable journey through Oaxaca City during the revered Dia de Los Muertos (Day of the Dead) holiday. Much preparation for the celebration takes place in October, and Rick gives us an insider’s look at the fiesta.

programme.title: Alberta, Canada
programme.desc: In Alberta, Canada, Donna’s first impression is- snow. And she enjoys it to the fullest. Donna finds myriad ways of taking advantage of a snowy environment, including snow-biking, ice walking, and staying at a world-renowned resort.

programme.title: From Peru to Tanzania
programme.desc: There are places on Earth worthy of absolute preservation and protection for all future generations. Meet people from Puerto Rico, Maryland, Peru, Tanzania, Slovakia, and Cambodia who all share an abiding belief in a sacred, healthy Earth.

programme.title: Unfair Game
programme.desc: Zambia and Eswatini (formerly Swaziland) represent two divergent strategies on environmentalism. Meet people from both countries and learn of the successes, failures, and sacrifices they experienced seeking environmental justice.

programme.title: The Mohawk Trail Across New England
programme.desc: The Mohawk Trail is deeply embedded in the history of America. For many years it served as a main trade route for indigenous tribes. As European settlement expanded, the Mohawk Trail began to change as the country itself changed. Tap into one of America’s richest springs of historical significance.

programme.title: The Iron Curtain Trail
programme.desc: For almost half a century, Europe was demonstrably divided into East and West by the "Iron Curtain,” an imaginary, yet strongly re-enforced, barrier separating Europe that stretched between the Barents and Black Seas. For 40 years, the Iron Curtain was a potent symbol of division between people.

programme.title: Los Angeles, My Own Heart of Darkness
programme.desc: Los Angeles, CA: New York chef, Anthony Bourdain, descends into the culinary underbelly of his metropolitan nemesis, Los Angeles, where he experiences the trials of celebrity fame and the joys of West Coast cuisine.

programme.title: So Much Vodka, So Little Time

programme.title: S8E12 - Todos Santos Magic
programme.desc: There is magic in the charming Baja town of Todos Santos. It all starts at the roadside bar Art and Beer. Then Rick checks into the Hotel California before meeting with Sergio Jaurequi, as well as Chefs Dona Ramona and Dany Lamote.

programme.title: Santa Barbara, California
programme.desc: Follow Donna to Santa Barbara, California, the “American Rivera,” and learn how to surf. Also, stay in an award-winning resort, and enjoy a dinner at restaurant that only uses organic local ingredients.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: France's Normandy
programme.desc: From a dramatic coast to rural pastures, this sweet section of France abounds with apple orchards, enchanting villages, stunning abbeys, and sparkling seaports. We base in the lovely seaside town Honfleur. At Giverny, and in the museums in Rouen and Honfleur, we discover the birth of Impressionism.

programme.title: Medieval Europe
programme.desc: The medieval world is one of the big draws of European Travel. Moody ruins, "tippy" towers, cobbled streets, sparkling mosaics, monasteries, castles, and cathedrals form the core of many a tourist's dreams. In this episode, we make sense out of a fascinating 1,000 years of history.

programme.title: Four Great Cities of Europe
programme.desc: Explore the world class European cities of London, Paris, Amsterdam, and Brussels. A European city bustles. It is a hub of commerce, the arts, energy, surprise, and international flavor. Where do you start if you have just 24-hours?

programme.title: S8E8 - Italy's Verona, Padova, and Ravenna
programme.desc: We'll visit three great cities in the shadow of Venice: Padova (Padua), with its university life and famed basilica; Verona and its Roman ruins; and Ravenna, for its shimmering mosaics.

programme.title: St. Augustine
programme.desc: First, we will take a sip from the distinctively tasting Fountain of Youth. Then we will touch the coquina walls of the undefeated Castillo San Marcos. Next, separate pirate truth from pirate myth at the appropriately named, Pirate Museum, and cure what ails us at the oldest General Store.

programme.title: Salt Lake City
programme.desc: Westward ho! We settle in Salt Lake City, where we learn about Brigham Young's settlement of the Utah territory and his monument at This is the Place Park. Then we dig in the dirt to find hundreds of perfectly preserved dinosaurs at the Utah Natural History museum.

programme.title: Adelaide South Australia
programme.desc: Jason visits Australia’s oldest winery in Adelaide and has a memorable dining experience in one of Australia’s top dining experiences, Restaurant Orana. For some sightseeing, he rides a bike through the sensational Barossa Valley.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: Disney Cruise Line
programme.desc: When Disney launched its first ship in 1998, The Disney Magic, it was unlike any other. Painted black to mimic classic ships from the age of cruising, the ship was decked out like only Disney could muster. Disney then bought an island in the Bahamas to serve as a destination for cruise guests only.

programme.title: Wild Travels: America's Most Unusual Festivals
programme.desc: When it is festival time, it is FUN time. Join Will Clinger and travel coast to coast to discover America’s most unique, enlightening, and unusual festivals. Get in the spirit, celebrate life, and pay homage to our shared cultural history.

programme.title: Italy: Part 1
programme.desc: Experience the arresting appeal and elegance of Italy in six select locations. Take an invigorating stroll along the Mediterranean coast in Castello Federiciano, marvel at Alberobello’s august trullo dry stone huts, and more.

programme.title: Tamales and Iguana, Oaxacan Style
programme.desc: Oaxaca, Mexico: Chef Tony Bourdain explores the exotic and colorful indigenous zone of Mexico's Oaxaca region where he tastes toasted grasshoppers and other delicacies. His adventure ends with mariachi music and, of course, lots of tequila.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: Walt Disney Resort Behind The Scenes
programme.desc: Since 1971, Walt Disney World has grown from a theme park and three hotels in Orlando, Florida to a vacation resort of unprecedented size and scope. Today the property encompasses four major theme parks, three water parks, 29 resort hotels, 99 holes of golf, two miniature golf courses, and more.

programme.title: Disneyland Resort: Behind the Scenes

programme.title: Ultimate Walt Disney World
programme.desc: Disney Parks are known for their unparalleled attractions, resorts, and vacation experiences, but when you think of Disney, do you think faced-paced, action-packed, adrenaline-pumping experiences? From the Tower of Terror to Mission Space, and Expedition Everest to Toy Story Mania, get “ultimate.”

programme.title: Tamales and Iguana, Oaxacan Style
programme.desc: Oaxaca, Mexico: Chef Tony Bourdain explores the exotic and colorful indigenous zone of Mexico's Oaxaca region where he tastes toasted grasshoppers and other delicacies. His adventure ends with mariachi music and, of course, lots of tequila.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: S9E1 - Oaxaca's Most Magical Holiday
programme.desc: Rick takes us on a remarkable journey through Oaxaca City during the revered Dia de Los Muertos (Day of the Dead) holiday. Much preparation for the celebration takes place in October, and Rick gives us an insider’s look at the fiesta.

programme.title: S9E2 - Oaxaca's Live-Fire Cooking
programme.desc: Everything tastes better when cooked over a fire, at least that is the Oaxacan credo. From soup to barbacoa, fiery embers influence the flavor of Oaxaca’s food in just the right ways. Join Rick in Oaxaca, San Felipe Usila, and Zaachilla.

programme.title: S9E3 - Off the Beaten Path in Huatulco
programme.desc: Mexico's beaches glimmer with pristine perfection. Chef Rick Bayless takes us off the beaten path to find great food and even better beaches such as Playa Chahue and Playa Principal. You would be well-advised to follow his lead.

programme.title: La Paz
programme.desc: Amid the dizzying heights of the Andes Mountains sits Laz Paz, Bolivia. The Mirandas, the friendly family Alexandra will be staying with, introduces her to elements of Bolivian culture that they keep close to their hearts. Also, meet famous Bolivian chola Glenda Yanez.

programme.title: Ganvie
programme.desc: Welcome to Ganvie, land of the unsubdued, the free, the resistance, and of peaceful waters. In Ganvie, the Tofinu people live on the water. To do so they must move at a careful pace, learn to live without excess, and form deep bonds of family and friendship to survive.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Join Alexandra as she visits with a friendly, forward-thinking family in Las Vegas, Nevada, a city certainly not built on winners (unless you become one), where anything is possible, and where water is so much of a precious resource the city employs water waste investigators.

programme.title: S7E1 - Rome: Ancient Glory
programme.desc: Focusing on the grandeur of classical Rome, we’ll marvel at the Colosseum, Pantheon, and Capitoline Museum before heading out on a bike ride along the ancient Appian Way.

programme.title: S7E2 - Rome: Baroque Brilliance
programme.desc: As we ramble through the heart of Rome, we’ll admire breathtaking Bernini statues and ponder sunbeams inside St. Peter’s Basilica. After dinner, we’ll take a nighttime stroll, lacing together the city’s piazzas and fountains.

programme.title: S7E3 - Rome: Back-Street Riches
programme.desc: We explore Rome on a more intimate scale — dodging Vespas in Trastevere, roaming through the historic Jewish Ghetto, and enjoying art treasures in a string of rarely visited churches to uncover the charms of hidden Rome.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance
programme.desc: In Florence, we'll revel in the genius of Michelangelo and Botticelli, climb the dome that kicked off the Renaissance, and cross the Arno to take in modern-day artisan life.

programme.title: S7E5 - Florentine Delights and on exciting Tuscan Side Trips
programme.desc: We enjoy Renaissance art in Florence, the city that propelled Europe out of the Middle Ages. Then we visit two cultural capitals in their own right: Pisa, where we’ll marvel at a tipsy tower; and Lucca, where we’ll celebrate Puccini.

programme.title: S7E6 - Paris: Regal and Intimate
programme.desc: In Paris, we'll cruise the Seine River, pay a visit to Napoleon’s tomb, and take in the majestic Louvre. Then we'll shop in a village-like neighborhood, attend church in a pipe organ loft, and celebrate Bastille Day.

programme.title: S7E7 - Paris: Embracing Life and Art
programme.desc: We'll ride a unicorn into the Middle Ages at Paris’ Cluny Museum, get a heavenly look at stained glass in Sainte-Chapelle, go on a tombstone pilgrimage at Pere Lachaise Cemetery, and savor the Parisian cafe scene.

programme.title: S7E8 - London: Historic and Dynamic
programme.desc: In London, we’ll ponder royal tombs in Westminster Abbey, discover treasures in the British Library, enjoy the vibrant evening scene in Soho, uncover Churchill’s secret WWII headquarters, and straddle the Prime Meridian at Greenwich.

programme.title: S7E9 - North England's Lake District and Durham
programme.desc: Hiking through the Cumbrian Lake District, we'll admire idyllic lakes, discover misty waterfalls, tour a slate mine, and climb up to a stony summit. Then we’ll play some cricket, hike Hadrian’s Wall, and be dazzled by Durham’s cathedral.

programme.title: S7E10 - Venice: City of Dreams
programme.desc: In Venice, we'll sample the splendor of the Doge's Palace, St. Mark's Basilica, Grand Canal, and masterpieces from the Venetian Renaissance — then take a glide on a gondola.

programme.title: S7E11 - Venice and Its Lagoon
programme.desc: We’ll start with a cruise through Venice’s lagoon, pausing to savor fresh fish canal-side. Then we’ll sample the treasures of the Accademia Gallery, explore some back-street wonders, and luxuriate in a venerable cafe on St. Mark’s Square.

programme.title: S7E12 - European Travel Skills Part 1
programme.desc: In this first of three shows focusing on European travel skills, we’ll visit the Netherlands and Germany to learn about transportation by train and car, changing money, and settling in upon arrival.

programme.title: S8E1 - Western Turkey
programme.desc: After kicking off in Kusadası, we wander ancient Ephesus, soak in a natural spa at Pamukkale, learn why dervishes whirl at Konya, and sail the Mediterranean on a "gulet" from Antalya.

programme.title: S8E2 - Central Turkey
programme.desc: In Turkey, we'll marvel at the fascinating landscape of Cappadocia from high above in a balloon...and from deep below, prowling an underground city where Christians once hid out.

programme.title: S8E3 - France’s Loire: Chateau Country
programme.desc: In France's Loire Valley, we'll visit four unique castles — elegant Chenonceau, massive Chambord, stately Cheverny, and fragrant Villandry — with fun stops along the way.

programme.title: S8E4 - Paris Side Trips
programme.desc: After roaming Versailles — the palace of palaces — we'll drop in on exquisite Vaux-le-Vicomte and extravagant Fontainebleau, marvel at Chartres Cathedral...and dine like kings.

programme.title: S8E5 - The Best of Israel
programme.desc: We'll discover the best of Israel, stopping in passionate, traditional Jerusalem, cosmopolitan Tel Aviv, the fortress of Masada, the Sea of Galilee, and the Yad Vashem memorial.

programme.title: S8E6 - Palestine
programme.desc: Exploring Palestine — the Muslim and Arab half of the Holy Land — we'll visit Jerusalem, harvest olives near Ramallah, follow pilgrims to Bethlehem, and bob in the Dead Sea.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: Cod Crazy
programme.desc: Portugal: Portuguese cuisine holds a dear place in Tony's culinary heart. Tony travels to Porto, home of the famous Port wine, where he is immediately exposed to the codfish and the almost mythical place it holds in Portuguese cuisine and culture.

programme.title: San Sebastian: A Food Lover's Town
programme.desc: San Sebastian, Spain: Tony explores the food-crazed Basque culture. Tony's guide, Chef Luis Irizar, takes Tony into the underworld of Basque gastronomic societies. Later, Tony explores the city's tapas bars.

programme.title: A Taste of Tokyo
programme.desc: Anthony travels to Tokyo, where he begins in the Tsujiki market and then is introduced to techniques in preparing edomae sushi. He also learns the diets of Sumo wrestlers.

programme.title: Dining With Geishas
programme.desc: Rural Japan: Tony decides to look for a more relaxing, traditional Japanese culinary experience in the countryside. Tony travels to an old-style Japanese inn that specializes in kaiseki cuisine, ancient tea ceremony, and local ingredients.

programme.title: Cobra Heart-Food That Makes You Manly
programme.desc: Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam: After taking a cyclo-ride through Ho Chi Minh City and trying various foods from roadside vendors and markets, Tony tests his might with a few shots of snake wine and a live cobra heart.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.title: My Hometown Favorites
programme.desc: New York, NY: Passionate about his city, Tony gives us an intimate tour of the New York City foods he loves - sturgeon and bagels, fluke ceviche, pan-seared foie gras, braised veal cheek, authentic cheese and, of course, a hotdog.

programme.title: San Sebastian: A Food Lover's Town
programme.desc: San Sebastian, Spain: Tony explores the food-crazed Basque culture. Tony's guide, Chef Luis Irizar, takes Tony into the underworld of Basque gastronomic societies. Later, Tony explores the city's tapas bars.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: So Much Vodka, So Little Time
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony continues his mission with a tour of local working-class specialties. He tries his hand at ice-fishing, drinks a lot of vodka, feasts on Russian foods, eats smoked fish and ends the outing with a dip in the outdoor cold pool.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

In last week's episode, Shea McIntee and the crew had a remarkable day of Marlin fishing in Madalena Bay. Now we find out Madalena Bay doesn't only have fantastic offshore fishing, it also has inshore fishing that is out of this world. Shea's captain takes us to some of his favorite spots to catch Red Snapper, Snook, Corbina, and a fish we have never seen before, Palometa.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake
programme.desc: Going camping and trout fishing in the Sierras is one of our favorite things to do. For the first time, Shea McIntee and the crew head down to South Lake Bishop. What makes this trip unique is that we get to fish with some good friends.

programme.title: Angling Buzz - Why America Loves Crappy

programme.title: Operation Fishing Freedom - Coast Guard Veteran Brad Peterson
programme.desc: Unsure of the path his life would take, Brad Peterson decided to join the U.S. Coast Guard. After saving many lives on the water as a part of rescue teams, Brad joined a new life-saving team as a nurse at the Minnesota VA. Today, we head out into the Gulf of Mexico to take Brad on his first saltwater fishing trip.

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.
